The calculateAnnualSalary method first calls calculateMonthlySalary to get the base monthly salary. It then multiplies it by 12 to get the annual salary. It adds any bonus and commission to the annual salary. Finally, it calculates the total salary after considering the applicable tax rate based on the employee's income bracket.

Note that the taxBrackets property is an array of objects that define the income ranges and the corresponding tax rates. The tax rate is applied to the income amount within each bracket.

