```javascript
function generateRandomString(length) {
  const lowercaseLetters = 'abcdefghijklmnopqrstuvwxyz';
  const uppercaseLetters = lowercaseLetters.toUpperCase();
  const digits = '0123456789';
  const specialCharacters = '!@#$%^&*()';

  const characters = lowercaseLetters + uppercaseLetters + digits + specialCharacters;

  let randomString = '';

  // Generate a random index to choose a character from the characters string
  function getRandomIndex(max) {
    return Math.floor(Math.random() * max);
  }

  // Helper function to check if a character is repeated consecutively
  function hasConsecutiveRepeatingCharacters(str) {
    for (let i = 0; i < str.length - 1; i++) {
      if (str[i] === str[i + 1]) {
        return true;
      }
    }
    return false;
  }

  // Add one of each required character type to the random string
  randomString += lowercaseLetters[getRandomIndex(lowercaseLetters.length)];
  randomString += uppercaseLetters[getRandomIndex(uppercaseLetters.length)];
  randomString += digits[getRandomIndex(digits.length)];
  randomString += specialCharacters[getRandomIndex(specialCharacters.length)];

  // Generate remaining characters
  for (let i = 0; i < length - 4; i++) {
    let newCharacter = characters[getRandomIndex(characters.length)];

    // Check if the new character is repeated consecutively, if so generate a new one
    while (hasConsecutiveRepeatingCharacters(randomString + newCharacter)) {
      newCharacter = characters[getRandomIndex(characters.length)];
    }

    randomString += newCharacter;
  }

  return randomString;
}

const randomString = generateRandomString(10);
console.log(randomString);
```

This code generates a random string of length N by choosing characters from the specified character types (lowercase letters, uppercase letters, digits, and special characters). It ensures that at least one character of each type is included in the generated string.

To optimize the code, we use a loop to generate the remaining characters after adding one of each required character type. We check if the newly generated character is repeated consecutively in the current string. If it is, we generate a new character until we find one that does not have consecutive repeating characters. This ensures that the generated string does not have consecutive repeating characters.

The time complexity of this code is O(N log N) because generating a random index using `Math.random()` has a time complexity of O(log N), and we perform this operation N times. The space complexity is O(N) because we store the generated string in a variable.

